<br>
<B>DO NOT ATTEMPT TO REPLY TO THIS THREAD.</B><br>
<br>
You should start a new topic on the "Applications for Membership" forum.<br>
<br>
The subject line for your new topic should be your character name, class and level<br>
<br>
The body of your message should clearly list the following information:<br>
<br>
1. Character Name<br>
2. Class<br>
3. Level (requirement: level 46)<br>
4. Guild, including positions held if appropriate<br>
5. Sponsor (if you have one, must be an existing member)<br>
6. Keys held<br>
7. Velious faction(s) you're allied with, if appropriate<br>
8. Why you want to join<br>
<br>
The moderators will periodically check this forum for new applicants, and will reply to your message saying whether your application has been accepted, or why it has been denied.<br>
<br>
Being a good raider involves paying attention and doing what you're told by the raid leader. Your application is your first opportunity to demonstrate to us that you can follow instructions. Applications titled 'I wanna join SCRAB' etc, will likely be ignored.<br>
<br>
If your application is accepted you should find you now have access to the member-only areas. You will not recieve a password, we utilise the EZBoard security options to grant you access. Your application will remain on the forum for one week for public scrutiny and comment before being moved to our dead messages archive.<br>
<br>
If your application is denied, the moderator should have given some indication as to the reason why. You will then have one week to edit your application to include any missing information and so forth, before your application is moved to our dead messages archive. If you fail to submit a satisfactory application in this time and still wish to join, you will need to reapply from scratch. <br>
